Ghoody Tagtreevivor Roborovski I recently saw Despicable Me 4, and I gotta say, it was kinda disappointing. The main villain, Maxime Le Mau, was never really super present within the movie and no real motive for wanting to kill Gru. Also, while watching the family try and adapt to their new lifestyle was fun, it left a lot of questions about Maxime, the school, and other things. One plus is that the babys arc was fun. I was glad to see that he turned good at the end and genuinely loved his father. Unfortunately, it was really only that moment and the moment where the child said dada that were really heartwarming. Other than that the baby was a BITCH! Anyways, another one of the new characters, Penny, was quite odd in every aspect. She was kinda rushed into the story, but I did like how she was introduced as an antagonist and later turned into the opposite. I also liked how they used her to move the plot forward as a way for the antagonist to gain the knowledge of Grus location. Too bad she didnt play a much bigger role outside of that. Also, the best part of the movie is the ending scene. Movie review of Despicable Me 4
